        "created_at": "2025-05-04T20:31:48.937Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hello, the category titled ‚ÄúUI/UX Feedback‚Äù is described as ‚ÄúShare thoughts and ideas on how the visual elements of Signal could be improved.‚Äù  (Category descriptions are visible when the user clicks on ‚ÄúAll categories,‚Äù but not, apparently, when the user clicks on the category it‚Äôs self‚Ä¶)  UX is an acronym for ‚ÄúUser experience.‚Äù  Per wikipedia, UX includes the user‚Äôs perceptions of utility, ease of use, and efficiency. While visual elements of an application certainly do impact UX, many other considerations also impact UX, such, as for example, the developer‚Äôs decision to brick the app thus locking the user out of access to all of their data, pending successful upgrade.  (This is not a hypothetical, this is something I have actually witnesses Signal to do in the past.)  I want to suggest that the scope of the ‚ÄúUI/UX Feedback‚Äù category should be expanded to include UX, or alternatively, a new category should be created for UX freedback, separate from UI feedback.</p>",
