        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/avitus/{size}/34172_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-05-04T22:19:54.506Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"openthedoorhal\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"68978\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/o/b3f665/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> openthedoorhal:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>the developer‚Äôs decision to brick the app thus locking the user out of access to all of their data, pending successful upgrade.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Keeping software current is an industry standard, not anything specific to Signal. If it can be resolved by updating to the newest version, which is presumably what the guidance is within the app when this happens (which it shouldn‚Äôt since auto-update is a thing), then it‚Äôs not ‚Äúbricked‚Äù.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"openthedoorhal\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"68978\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/o/b3f665/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> openthedoorhal:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I want to suggest that the scope of the ‚ÄúUI/UX Feedback‚Äù category should be expanded to include UX</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>It does. It‚Äôs in the category name. What you actually want is an update to the category description.</p>",
