        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/o/b3f665/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-05-05T10:03:58.920Z",
        "cooked": "<p>The given description references, or we could even say, defines, ‚ÄúUI/UX‚Äù as ‚Äúvisual elements.‚Äù  You say that this is not the definition that this board is using for this term, but for some reason, you don‚Äôt want to fix the definition that is provided.  If your purpose here is to insult my intelligence and gaslight me, you are succeeding.  If your purpose is to help the UI/UX of this board be reasonably good and effective, I would argue that in this particular instance, you are not succeeding.  In reading the given description, I (mis)understood that this category of the board is only for the ‚Äúvisual‚Äù aspects of UX.  Why do you have to be so obtuse about this?  If you have access to improve the definition, then improve it.  If you don‚Äôt have access to improve it, then please tell me who does.  And please, never again reply to another of my posts.  Thank you.</p>",
