        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Meteor0id\" data-post=\"9\" data-topic=\"68978\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/meteor0id/48/55420_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Meteor0id:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Same with the new translators (who are hired through some company), most of them never directly interact</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>As far as I‚Äôve seen, translation feedback has often gotten a response quite quickly. I believe <a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/rassilon1963\">@rassilon1963</a>  recently had some feedback that was taken into consideration pretty much immediately. (please correct me, if I‚Äôm wrong there)</p>",
